06580nam a22010455i 9783110922370DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20122006gw     fo  d z      ger d  a97831109223707 a10.1515/97831109223702doi  a(DE-B1597)46140  a(OCoLC)979946838  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 ager  agwcDE 4aPN56.M535bB87 2006 7aLIT0041702bisacsh04a809/.93355223  aGK 10522rvk0(DE-625)rvk/40736:00aBürgerlichkeit im 18. Jahrhundert /chrsg. von Hans Edwin Friedrich, Fotis Jannidis, Marianne Willems. 1aTübingen : bMax Niemeyer Verlag, c[2012] 4c©2006  a1 online resource (403 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aStudien und Texte zur Sozialgeschichte der Literatur ,x0174-4410 ;v1050 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aBürgerlichkeit and Bürger are central concepts in (German) literary history. The emancipation of the Bürgertum (bourgeoisie/middle classes) in the modern age has in fact been identified as the prime source of the profound cultural and socio-structural changes taking place in the 18th century. However, close scrutiny of the historical circumstances has split up the apparently close-knit concept of the Bürger into a diversity of semantic and socio-structural components that appear to be anything but unified. Accordingly, traditional models operative in literary history and sociology need to be thoroughly reviewed and revised.  aBürgerlichkeit und Bürger sind zentrale Konzepte der Literaturgeschichte. Die tiefgreifenden kulturellen und sozialstrukturellen Veränderungen des 18. Jahrhunderts sind auf die Emanzipation des neuzeitlichen Bürgertums zurückgeführt worden. Die Untersuchung der historischen Verhältnisse hat jedoch den so kompakt scheinenden Begriff des Bürgers in eine semantische wie sozialstrukturelle Vielfalt aufgelöst, deren Einheit mehr denn je fraglich ist. Die gängigen literarhistorischen und soziologischen Modelle bedürfen daher einer grundlegenden Revision.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman literaturey18th centuryxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aLiterature, Moderny18th centuryxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aMiddle class in literaturevCongresses. 4aBürgertum ‹Motiv›. 4aDeutsch. 4aGeschichte 1700-1813. 4aKongress. 4aLiteratur. 70(DE-588)4005248-50(DE-627)1063823650(DE-576)208859918aBegriff2gnd 70(DE-588)4035964-50(DE-627)1062450150(DE-576)209015608aLiteratur2gnd 70(DE-588)4055772-80(DE-627)1061568450(DE-576)20911536XaSozialgeschichte2gnd 70(DE-588)4069722-80(DE-627)1061026990(DE-576)209177756aBürgertum2gnd 70(DE-588)4122925-30(DE-627)1057588920(DE-576)209555386aBildungsbürgertum2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aFriedrich, Hans Edwin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFriedrich, Hans-Edwin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHahn, Alois, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJannidis, Fotis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJannidis, Fotis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLinke, Angelika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLüsebrink, Hans-Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaurer, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCarthy, John A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMellmann, Katja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPikulik, Lothar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReinhardt, Hartmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRu